Appendix A: ‘Hot' versus ‘Cold' Admin Tasks</Heading-1>
<pagenum>
<A ID="pgfId-1038380"></A>
280</pagenum>
<Body>
<A ID="pgfId-1038004"></A>
'Hot' admin tasks are defined as tasks that take effect immediately and do not require the server to restart. 'Cold' admin tasks are defined as tasks that require one or more instances of the server to restart to reflect the changes.</Body>
<Body>
<A ID="pgfId-1038005"></A>
In an Enterprise Edition clustered deployment, 'cold' tasks will require one or more hosts in the cluster to restart their instance of MarkLogic Server in order to reflect the changes. In an Enterprise Edition single-server deployment and in all Standard Edition deployments, 'cold' tasks will cause MarkLogic Server to restart in order to reflect the changes. </Body>
<Body>
<A ID="pgfId-1038231"></A>
